<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>TRANSPORT SELECT COMMITTEE – HIGHWAYS AGENCY</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Written evidence from the Highways Agency (WRT 013)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:30.83pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">INTRODUCTION</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45pt; text-indent:-45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">1.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Highways Agency is responsible for the strategic road network in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">England</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, covering more than 4,300 miles of motorways and trunk roads.  The Agency delivers a robust </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">winter service that has been developed over a number of years, with significant improvements introduced following previous reviews and lessons learned.  The Agency is well prepared for winter weather.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:30.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">BACKGROUND</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Resilience of the Strategic Road Network</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2.1.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Ensuring resilience of the strategic road network is a challenge during times of severe weather</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, especially as </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">weather conditions can be unpredictable and change quickly.  High traffic volumes and congestion, particularly at peak times, can make keeping th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e network open during severe weather difficult.  However, this is what the Agency aims to achieve and it has done so consistently over recent years with only very isolated problems at times of exceptionally extreme weather.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2.1.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Following a spell of particularly cold and snowy weather in mid-late January 2013 the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">RAC</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Foundation commissioned a review into how highway authorities coped with the conditions.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The report, entitled ‘</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Ploughing On: A review of highway resilience in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Winter</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> 2013</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">also </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">consider</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">response to the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">further heavy snow in March, which was the coldest for 51 years.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">report </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">comment</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ed </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">that “…the Highways Agency responded well to the recent periods of snow and ice</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">”.  It </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">also concluded that</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, due to the impleme</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ntation of the recommendations from various reviews, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">there is much stronger underlying </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">resilience than </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">was the case in 2009-10</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Lessons Learn</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> and Changes Made</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2.2.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">One of the most significant changes made since the winter of 2009-10 has been the establishme</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">nt of a strategic salt stockpile</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, which has substantially increased the resilience of salt stocks</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.  This has been delivered by the Highways Agency in conjunction with the Department, following the recommendations of the Independent Review of England’s Transport System in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Winter</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> (2010).  Over 500,000 tonnes of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">salt</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> were imported into </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">England</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> in the win</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ter of 2010-11 which helped to provide </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">resilience at a time of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">widespread </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">salt shortage.  Since then, the Agency has continued to maintain strategic stockpiles amounting to 425,000 tonnes, of which 12</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">0</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,000 tonnes </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">(representing 6.7 capability days</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">are all</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ocated for the strategic road network and around 305,000 tonnes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> held </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">for local authorities.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The strategic stockpile will only be used as a last resort in the event that domestic salt </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">supplies are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">unable to meet demand</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and as such </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">continues to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">play a key r</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ole in ensuring a high level of resilience in national salt stocks.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2.2.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Highways Agency has implemented many </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">other </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">improvements since the winter of 2009-10, based on a robust lessons learned process and imple</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">me</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ntation of the recommendations from</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> winter resilience </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">reviews including the Transport Select </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Committee report </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">‘Keeping the UK Moving: The Impact on Transport of the Winter Weather in December 2010’.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The improvements made have </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">also </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">taken</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> knowledge and learning </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">gained </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">from our active role on</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the winter service technical committee of the World Road Association together with our partnership agreement with the Netherlands and Belgium. In addition we share experiences and lessons nationally with transport operators of other modes including </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">N</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">al </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">R</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ail, T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ransport for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">London</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and airports</span><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> I</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">mprovements include:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-27pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">New Winter Fleet</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Completion </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">(in June 2010) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">of the roll-out of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the Agency’s new fleet of 437 specialised </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">winter service </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">vehicles.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> These spread pre-wetted salt which acts more quickly</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">stays on the road longer</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, delivering a more effective and sustainable treatment. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">vehicles</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> are all equipped with data logging systems which, in addition to GPS location information, record vehicle speed, salt spread rates, ploughing condition and other </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">vehicle operating conditions.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-27pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">b)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Salt Stock Management</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Improvements to operational salt stock management, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">resilience</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">monitoring</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> has taken place</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, allowing early identification of salt stock issues.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">  The</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Agency’s </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">stock monitoring sy</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">tem</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> is a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">lso use</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">d</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the Department and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">local highway authorities</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to give a better full national picture.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-27pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">c)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Severe Weather Plans</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">he Agency’s severe weather plans</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> which </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">our </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">service providers are required to complete each year</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> for each area</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, have undergone substantial revision</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Improvements include the identification of vulnerable locations on the network, which are particularly susceptible to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">disruption from severe weather</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. Key transport hubs such as Heathrow and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Manchester</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> airports are considered in the preparation of the pla</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ns</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Mitigation plans are in place to deal with problems at these locations and may include measures such as pre-positioning of salt spreaders with ploughs, traffic officer and heavy recovery vehicles, multi-agency response arrangements (police</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">local au</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">thorities) and contingency plans. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">An example is the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">multi-agency response </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">plan in place for the A38 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Haldon</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Hill and A328 Telegraph Hill in Devon, just south of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Exeter</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, which was successfully implemented several times during the 2012-13 winter season.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Furt</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">her improvements </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">made </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to the severe weather plans include the provision of guidance for treating the network in extreme cold conditions and additional measures to ensure the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">resilience</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> of Agency depots.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-27pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">d)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Highways Agency Weather Information Service</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">For the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> 2012-13 winter season t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">he Agency introduced its new </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">weather i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">nformation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ervice, which </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">takes data from more than 240 weather stations on the strategic road network, together with forecast information, and makes that information available to its service pr</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">oviders and others to enable them to make informed decisions on how to respond to severe weather. I</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">n addition, the Agency has a Met Office forecaster embedded in the National Traffic Operations Centre during the winter period</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> which</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> enables</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> us</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to send out t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">argeted severe weather warnings and alerts to all interested stakeholders </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">so that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">appropriate actions </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">can</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> be taken</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">  We </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">provide the Met Office (and other </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">partners)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">with</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">all</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">observation data and camera imagery</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">received from </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">our</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> weather stations under a defi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ned data exchange agreement</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-27pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Amber Alert Process</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">he Agency introduced an ‘amber alert’ process for snow in 2011 that provides freight operators and others with advance targeted notice of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">when there is a significant risk of disruption to the network from snow. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">This is supported by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">variable </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">message signs on the network to provide advance warning to road users of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">when </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">severe weather</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> is expected.  This is</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> supplemented by messages on the Agency</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">’s website and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">social media.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-27pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">f)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Communications &amp; Marketing Campaign</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Since winter 2009/10, the Highways Agency has undertaken a comprehensive partnership marketing campaign and has worked closely with over 100 key partners</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">- including the AA, RAC, Institute </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">of Advanced Motorists (IAM), Road Haulage Association (RHA) and the Freight Transport Association (FTA), local authorities</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> airports to deliver winter messages through partners’ own communications channels, such as websites, newsletters, posters and soc</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ial media channels.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">  Each year t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">he Agency continues to implement a comprehensive winter communication campaign</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> working with key partners including the Met Office and Cabinet Office as part of the wider ‘</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Get ready for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Winter</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">’ campaign. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-27pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">g)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Use of Social </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Media</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Agency has also developed its use of social media including its dedicated winter twitter channel (@</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">winterhighways</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">) and has introduced a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Facebook</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> page at </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Facebook.com/</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">winterhighways</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. These media </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">help</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the Agency to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">put across key messages, includi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ng information on road conditions and weather alerts, to a wider audience than before.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-27pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">h)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Crisis Management Manual</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Highways Agency Crisis Management Manual (CMM) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">is an internal document </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">launched in November 2011 and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">last </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">updated in July 2013. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">It sets ou</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">t policy and guidance for how the Agency </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and its service providers </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">manage severe disruptive events that affect the strategic road network. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Key changes relate to management and reporting </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in advance of, and during, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">widespread events, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">availability of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">crisis management expertise and business continuity.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2.2.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Although numerous improvements have been made to the way the Highways Agency plans for and responds to severe winter weather, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">we accept the need to avoid </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">complacency. The Agency has a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> well</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> established lessons learned programme </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">specifically </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">for winter service, which feeds into the issue of the latest Severe Weather Plan for each area. In this way the Agency continuously review</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> its performance, learning lessons from each winter period, and m</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">aking improvements.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Preparedness for Winter 2013/1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">4</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2.3.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Highways Agency is well prepared for the coming winter.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">O</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">perational salt stocks </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">will stand at </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">around 270,000 tonnes </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">(representing 15 capability days) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">by the end of October, in line with the past </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">two years</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, and more than at the start of the 2010-11 season.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">  In addition we continue to hold 120,000 tonnes of strategic salt.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2.3.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Agency is currently finalising its preparations for its winter driving campaign ‘Make time for winter’, which will commenc</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e on 28 October. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">campaign </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">will</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> encourage road users to prepare for their journeys, to plan by checking traffic and weather before they set out and then to adjust their travel plans and their driving style according to the conditions.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> We are working wi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">th key partners and stakeholders to maximise the reach of the campaign and to increase the impact of messages. Partner agencies such as DVLA and VOSA/DSA are supporting this with their own communications channels</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.  W</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e are working with motoring organisation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s, freight transport organisations, the Confederation of Passenger Transport, local authorities and a number of large private sector organisations to help promote the key messages of "Be prepared: is your vehicle ready for winter?" and "Be informed: have y</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ou checked the latest traffic and weather?"</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2.3.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Following the experience of running the campaign in previous winters </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the Agency</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> will be increasing the flexibility of the campaign so we can respond quickly to the different challenges of varying weather pattern</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s. Our significant use of online communications and social media is particularly suited to this type of agile and responsive campaign</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">  Our media spokespeople </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">also</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> play an important role </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">du</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ring peak periods of severe weather by providing interviews to the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">media</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, both broadcast and press.  W</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e will also facilitate </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">media </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">visits to our control centres and depots where it is appropriate to do so and does not compromise operational delivery</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2.3.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Highways Agency campaign sits within the wider cross-government </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">‘Get Ready for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Winter</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">’ </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">campaign. This is hosted by the Met Office and co-ordinated by the Cabinet Office to include key Government departments/agencies, the health and voluntary sectors to provide advice and support on a wide range of weather related issue</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Links between the partners will further increase the reach of our particular messages related to travel during severe weather.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Coordinating Responses</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2.4.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Agency recognises the importance of coordinating its planning and operational response with othe</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">r authorities, such as the police and local highway authorities.  Severe weather plans require service providers to consult with adjacent local authorities to ensure, among other things, that planned treatment routes are coordinated and that there is shari</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ng of information on treatment </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">decision</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> making.  Local authorities take part in annual </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">severe weather desk exer</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">cises and briefings are provided.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2.4.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">There is an established procedure for the provision of mutual aid during the winter season.  For example, last</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> winter the Agency provided a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">snow plough</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and driver to Cumbria County Council to assist wit</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">h</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> snow clearance </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">following</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> heavy snowfalls at the end of March. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">In some locations salt barns are shared with local authorities </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">which</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> provides a benefit to both par</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ties. Furthermore, the Agency works with police and local highway authorities as part of Local Resilience Forums, which play a key coordination role at times of significant disruption to the network from any cause, including severe weather.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">October 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> One capability day is based on 6 treatments of 20g per sq metre on all routes which is considered to be the maximum scale of treatment under the most extreme weather conditions.</span></p></body></html>